{% extends "base.html.j2" %}
{% block title %}API Key {{ "Created" if mode == "mint" else "Rotated" }} · WisprAlt Admin{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
{% if mode == "mint" %}
  <h1>API key created for "{{ program_name }}"</h1>
  <p><strong>Copy the token now — it won't be shown again.</strong></p>
{% else %}
  <h1>API key rotated for "{{ program_name or label }}"</h1>
  <p><strong>The old token is invalid. Paste the new one into the program now.</strong></p>
{% endif %}

<h2>Token</h2>
<pre><code>{{ plaintext }}</code></pre>

<h2>How to use it (OpenAI-compatible)</h2>
<p>In any program that speaks the OpenAI Whisper API, set these two environment variables:</p>
<pre><code>export OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://transcribe.integrateapi.ai/v1
export OPENAI_API_KEY={{ plaintext }}</code></pre>

<p>Then any OpenAI Whisper client (Python <code>openai</code> SDK, Node <code>openai</code> SDK, Buzz, MacWhisper, Open WebUI voice mode, etc.) will route to WisprAlt instead of OpenAI's servers.</p>

<p>See <a href="/admin/keys">Integration Keys</a> · <a href="/admin/">Dashboard</a></p>
{% endblock %}
